author: Joel Odom | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Beavers edged by Buffaloes: Describe game in 5 words or less
text:
Nick Mitchell and Ryan Nall brought a different look to the Oregon State Beavers offense on Saturday night, but it was a familiar result as the Beavers lost to Colorado 17-13 and fell to 0-4 in Pac-12 play and 2-5 overall.
Few would have expected a huge chunk of Oregon State victories under first-year head coach Gary Andersen , but the Buffaloes likely represented the Beavers' best chance for a conference victory. OSU's remaining schedule looks like this: at Utah, versus UCLA, at Cal, versus Washington, and at Oregon.
What stands out the most after this matchup of the Pac-12's cellar-dwellers? Write the headline of this game by jumping into the comments section below and describing the game in five words or less.
